on according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":9,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":18,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":63,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Malovell was born about 1319, in Haughton, Nottinghamshire, England, her father, Stephen Malovell, was 32 and her mother, Elizabeth Lexington, was 32. She had at least 2 sons with John Stanhope."},"et":{"about 1319–":"umbes 1319–Surnud","1319–Female":"1319–Surnud","1319–Male":"1319–Surnud","1368–1436":"1368–1436","1379–1432":"1379–1432","1289–1322":"1289–1322","1289–1321":"1289–1321","1382":"1382","1337":"1337","1436":"1436","about 1319":"umbes 1319","1368":"1368","1379":"1379","1322":"1322","1289":"1289","1432":"1432","1453":"1453","1321":"1321","10 Mar 2003":"10. märts 2003","about 1379":"umbes 1379","1319":"1319","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Haughton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Haughton, Nottinghamshire, England"